          "body": "Verses 15-23 shift from union/baptism to slavery. The argument is parallel but the angle is different. Paul's claim is that *every human being is a slave*; there is no third option called autonomy. You are either a slave of sin (whose wages is death, 6:23) or a slave of righteousness/God (whose outcome is eternal life). The believer's freedom from sin (6:18, 22) is *not* freedom from all masters — it is enslavement to a new and good Master. Paul knows this image strains modern sensibilities (he apologizes for it in 6:19, 'I speak in human terms'), but he refuses to abandon it because it tells the truth about human existence: we always serve."
